folder: 149th Street (East) & Anthony J. Griffin Place, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: 149th Street (East) - Anthony J. Griffin Place
text:
(1) East 149th Street, north side, west from Anthony J. Griffin Place to Grand Concourse, showing the Mott Haven auto wrecking yard and an old diner.
(2) Shows a closeup. On this side, there was later erected the Bronx Central Annex Post Office.
P. L. Sperr  August 28, 1930
No Reproductions  Views 1,2

folder: 149th Street (East) & Anthony J. Griffin Place, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: 149th Street (East) - Anthony J. Griffin Place
text:
E. 149th Street, north side east from Anthony J. Griffin Place. At this point the street is above the New York Central and New Haven railroad tracks. The tall building is the ten-story Terminal Building, near the northeast corner of Park Avenue. View 2 shows the low building at the northeast corner of Park Avenue. View 3 is east from the Terminal Building.

P. L. Sperr  April 28, 1941
Views 1, 2, 3
